A 60-year-old woman is in critical condition after a purse snatcher shoved her to the ground outside of a supermarket in a quiet Queens neighborhood Saturday morning, NYPD said. An unidentified man approached the woman outside of the Key Food supermarket on 73rd Avenue in Bayside around 9:30 a.m., cops said. The brute grabbed her purse and allegedly pushed the woman, who hit her head on ground. She was transported to North Shore University Hospital in critical condition, police said. The suspect drove off from the scene in a white Honda, according to cops. No arrests have been made.